name: Endurance + 10min Best Effort
description:
Producing peak power late in the race is a critical element of performance. 



After warming up, the workout provides you with a block of free-riding where the aim is to ride within zones 2 to 3. This period of riding serves to build fatigue and deplete vital glycogen stores. 



The session is then completed with a 10 minute 'best effort'. The aim is for this effort to be close to your FTP power.
